      public char checkIfAlpha​(char input)
      Checks if the char input into the function is part of the alphabet, if it is then the function will output ~ to represent a member of the alphabet, if not then it returns the char.
      Parameters:
      input - represents an individual character in a string of equations
      Returns:
      a char that represents if it is alphabetical which is represented by the ~ sign, or returns the char if the input is not part of the alphabet.
